<h1 class="hero-h">How much does AI marketing cost? <em>2026 reference.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">AI marketing costs split across tooling, AI-augmented agencies, and internal time. Here is the realistic 2026 budget for B2B teams at each stage, and where the money actually goes.</p>
<div class="verdict"><div class="verdict-l">Short answer</div><p class="verdict-p">A solo marketer's AI stack costs $50 to $200 per month. A mid-market B2B marketing team's AI stack costs $300 to $1,500 per month. An AI-augmented marketing agency runs $5,000 to $30,000 per month. Most teams overspend on tools and underspend on the time to learn them.</p></div>
<p class="note">Pricing references are as of June 2026 and may change. Always confirm current pricing on the vendor site before committing.</p>
</div></div>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">The pricing tiers</h2>
<p class="body">Four cost categories make up the bulk of an AI marketing budget:</p>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Foundation assistant ($20 to $30 / seat / month).</strong> Claude Pro or Team, ChatGPT Plus or Team. The base on which everything else sits.</li>
<li><strong>Marketing-tuned tools ($30 to $500 / month).</strong> Jasper, Copy.ai, Writer, or similar; plus AI features in your CMS, email tool, and CRM.</li>
<li><strong>Workflow and orchestration ($30 to $200 / month).</strong> Zapier, Make, or n8n for connecting AI to your other tools.</li>
<li><strong>Agency or fractional support ($5,000 to $30,000 / month, optional).</strong> An AI-augmented marketing agency or a fractional marketing leader who uses AI throughout.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">What drives the number up or down</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Team size.</strong> Per-seat tools scale linearly with marketers.</li>
<li><strong>Output volume.</strong> Heavier content production drives higher token and seat usage.</li>
<li><strong>Channel mix.</strong> Paid acquisition, organic content, and lifecycle marketing each have their own AI tool requirements.</li>
<li><strong>In-house capability.</strong> A team that can build its own Projects and prompts spends less on standalone AI marketing products.</li>
<li><strong>Agency or fractional support.</strong> Optional but often the biggest single line item.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Where it fits the cost ladder</h2>
<table class="cmp-table">
<thead><tr><th>Option</th><th>Typical cost</th><th>Best when</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>Solo marketer AI stack</td><td>$50 to $200 / month</td><td>One-person marketing team</td></tr>
<tr><td>Mid-market team AI stack</td><td>$300 to $1,500 / month</td><td>5 to 25 marketers</td></tr>
<tr><td>AI-augmented agency</td><td>$5,000 to $30,000 / month</td><td>Channel execution with AI throughout</td></tr>
<tr><td>Fractional CMO with AI</td><td>$8,000 to $25,000 / month</td><td>Strategy plus AI execution</td></tr>
<tr><td>Full-time AI marketing hire</td><td>$120K to $200K / year all-in</td><td>In-house AI ownership</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Who should pay for it</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Spend on the foundation assistant first.</strong> A Claude or ChatGPT seat per marketer is the single highest-leverage spend.</li>
<li><strong>Skip standalone marketing AI products until</strong> a marketer proves the foundation assistant cannot do the job. Most can.</li>
<li><strong>Pay for an AI-augmented agency when</strong> the channel execution is bigger than your team can absorb.</li>
<li><strong>Budget for the time to learn, not just the tools.</strong> Underspending here is the most common mistake.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Frequently asked questions</h2>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Will AI marketing tools replace my agency?</div><div class="faq-a">Sometimes. AI augments execution-heavy agencies more than it replaces them; the agency relationship is also strategy and brand-management work that AI does not substitute for.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How much should I budget per marketer?</div><div class="faq-a">$30 to $60 per seat per month for foundation assistant and adjacent tools. Above that, you are paying for marketing-specific products you may or may not need.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Are AI marketing platforms worth their premium?</div><div class="faq-a">Sometimes, for teams that value pre-built marketing workflows and brand voice management. Often no for teams comfortable building their own Projects and prompts.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What is the most underspent line item?</div><div class="faq-a">Time. The team that gets eight hours of training and three weeks to build prompt libraries outperforms the team that buys an expensive product and never sets it up.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How current are these numbers?</div><div class="faq-a">As of June 2026. Vendor pricing changes; budget annually and reconcile actuals every 90 days.</div></div>
</div></section>

